abstract: The Senate Press Gallery just off the chamber was largely empty — a stark contrast to the last two weeks, when reporters crammed into every available seat.
snippet: The Senate Press Gallery just off the chamber was largely empty — a stark contrast to the last two weeks, when reporters crammed into every available seat.
lead_paragraph: With the debate over witnesses finished and a not-guilty verdict for President Trump all but assured, senators began arriving Monday morning for closing arguments by the House managers and the president’s legal defense team. Each side will have two hours to bring their case to an end.
headline_main: The trial resumes, but with little of the intensity and drama that gripped the Capitol last week.

abstract: The Connecticut opera singer who drew gunfire when she smashed an SUV through security checkpoints outside President Donald Trump's Florida home is mentally ill and wasn't taking her medication before leading a trooper on a wild chase, her attorney told a judge Monday.
snippet: The Connecticut opera singer who drew gunfire when she smashed an SUV through security checkpoints outside President Donald Trump's Florida home is mentally ill and wasn't taking her medication before leading a trooper on a wild chase, her attorne...
lead_paragraph: FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. — The Connecticut opera singer who drew gunfire when she smashed an SUV through security checkpoints outside President Donald Trump's Florida home is mentally ill and wasn't taking her medication before leading a trooper on a wild chase, her attorney told a judge Monday.
headline_main: Attorney: Mar-a-Lago Checkpoint Crasher Is Mentally Ill
headline_print_headline: Attorney: Mar-a-Lago Checkpoint Crasher Is Mentally Ill

abstract: A closer look at our election forecaster before the Iowa caucuses.
snippet: A closer look at our election forecaster before the Iowa caucuses.
lead_paragraph: Shortly before 9 p.m. Eastern on Monday, we expect the first returns from the Iowa Democratic caucuses. If you choose to follow the results live tonight, we hope you’ll do it with us: We’ll have results, analysis from our reporters and interactive maps.

lead_paragraph: DUBAI, United Arab Emirates — Days after Gulf Arab states expressed their support for President Donald Trump's efforts at resolving the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, representatives from these same countries and other Muslim nations gathered in Saudi Arabia and rejected the White House's plan as “biased.”
headline_main: Muslim Nations Reject Trump's Mideast Plan in Saudi Meeting
headline_print_headline: Muslim Nations Reject Trump's Mideast Plan in Saudi Meeting
